.TH "netlink_ns_capable" 9 "netlink_ns_capable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
netlink_ns_capable \- General netlink message capability test
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" netlink_ns_capable
.BI "(const struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "struct user_namespace *user_ns "  ","
.BI "int cap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
socket buffer holding a netlink command from userspace
.IP "user_ns" 12
The user namespace of the capability to use
.IP "cap" 12
The capability to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Test to see if the opener of the socket we received the message
from had when the netlink socket was created and the sender of the
message has the capability \fIcap\fP in the user namespace \fIuser_ns\fP.
